on 4 level tablespoon-size mounds, 5 cm apart, onto prepared baking tray. With your fingers, gently spread mounds into flat circles and an even thickness. Bake for 4-6 minutes (180°C), or until bubbly and lightly golden. Allow Parmesan crisps to cool slightly (approx. 40 seconds). While still warm and pliable, gently remove with a palette knife and press and form each crisp over moulds, until hardened. Transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely. Repeat with remaining mixture to make approx. 24 baskets. Set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Transfer mousse into a piping bag fitted with a 1 cm fluted nozzle. Pipe a rosette of mousse into each Parmesan basket. Top with a little of the apple, beetroot, walnuts and micro herbs (optional). Serve immediately. "}],"hintsAndTricks":["A mandolin can be used to easily cut your apple into matchsticks.","You can use shot glasses, wine corks, miniature muffin tins or small, handleless espresso cups to mould your baskets.","This dish is best served on the day it's made."],"basicInfo":["easy","1h 15m","1h 15m","24 portions"]}